In MSTest v4, `[ExpectedException]` is removed. Replace it with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()` inside the test body:

```csharp
// Before (v3)
[ExpectedException(typeof(InvalidOperationException))]
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest()
{
    MyCall();
}

// After (v4)
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<InvalidOperationException>(() => MyCall());
}
```

**For async tests**, use `Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>()`:

```csharp
await Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<HttpRequestException>(
    () => client.GetAsync(url));
```

**If you used `AllowDerivedTypes = true`**, use `Assert.Throws<T>()` / `Assert.ThrowsAsync<T>()` instead (matches derived exception types).

> **Tip:** MSTest v3 analyzer `MSTEST0006` flags `[ExpectedException]` usage â€” you can adopt `Assert.ThrowsExactly` while still on v3 to prepare for the upgrade.

